Troubleshooting — Browser Cannot Reach

Possible causes:

Host firewall blocking 8080

Cloud security group blocking port

Container not actually running

Port already in use

Docker running inside VM (wrong IP)

Nginx not listening on 0.0.0.0

SELinux blocking

Wrong bind address

Wrong network mode

Debug Steps

Check container:

docker ps

Check port binding:

docker port <container_id>

Inspect networking:

docker inspect <container_id>

Check listening ports:

ss -tulnp | grep 8080

Test locally:

curl localhost:8080

Test inside container:

docker exec -it <container_id> sh
curl localhost

Check logs:

docker logs <container_id>
